# Order to learn

## You need to open the files in the following order and understand the code as written in the comment section

## Basic : 

1) Hello_World.cpp

2) Hello_World_new.cpp

3) input.cpp

4) cctype Module usage for character classification - classification_of_characters.cpp

5) Way to know data type of a variable - typeinfo.cpp

6) if_else.cpp -> swapping.cpp

7) switch.cpp

8) ternary_operator.cpp

9) increment_decrement.cpp

10) for_nesting.cpp -> more_control_variables_in_for.cpp -> triangle_matrix.cpp

11) while_loop.cpp -> loop_termination_within_loop.cpp -> repeating_computation_using_while.cpp

12) scope.cpp

13) continue_break_statement.cpp

14) scientific_format.cpp

15) constant_variable.cpp -> constant-variable.cpp

16) goto.cpp : goto keyword

17) initializing_array.cpp : Introduction to arrays and way to declare and define them

18) print_read_array.cpp

19) zero_trail_in_array.cpp 

20) multidimensional_array.cpp -> three_dimensional_array.cpp

21) enum_n_array.cpp

22) defining_function.cpp -> swap_function.cpp

23) void_function.cpp

24) scope_in_functions.cpp

25) default_para.cpp

26) function_overloading.cpp

Rest can be Done as Wish
